</head><body><table width=90% align=center><tr><td class=textbody><center><h1>Damage Focus Items - A Wizard's Listing</h1><br>by Whizbang Dustyboots</center><br>(Translated from the original Gnomish, Edition 1.04)
<br><br>

<I>To answer the reoccurring question that so many wizards, including myself, have asked -- "where do I get a damage focus that will help me with my damage spells?" -- I visited the libraries of Ak'Anon, Erudin, Kaesora and Skyshrine, as well as entering into correspondence with wizards from all over Norrath, Luclin and the Planes of Power. This listing, humble as it may be, is the result. I hope it may be of some use to my fellow wizards.<br><br>

While compiling this list, I noticed something I had been woefully ignorant of in the past, and I apologize to my magician friends for my oversight: At the same level an improved damage focus effect stops working, magicians are able to summon their next damage focus bracelet. The arcanist Gallenite's intention, in other words, was quite clearly to create a closer and more symbiotic bond between the wizarding and magical communities, and it is to my chagrin that I did not recognize this previously. I salute you, Gallenite, for your foresight in this matter and may your goal come to pass.<br><br>

Thank you for your kind attention and please write me, in care of Ak'Anon's Library Mechanamagica, if you have any additions or corrections for me to make to this listing.<br><br>

Yours in Gnome Power,<br>
<a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank">Whizbang Dustyboots</a></I>

